This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of computational linguistics (cs.CL) because it focuses on cognitive theories of human language processing and the analysis of fMRI data related to language processing. Additionally, the paper discusses the decoding of concepts from brain signals, which is a common topic in natural language processing research.

The paper also involves the use of machine learning techniques, which suggests that it could be relevant to the sub-categories of neural networks (cs.NE) and machine learning (cs.LG). 

Furthermore, the paper discusses the use of clustering and relational analyses, which could be relevant to the sub-category of computer vision (cs.CV) as well as artificial intelligence (cs.AI). 

Overall, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL, followed by cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.CV, and cs.AI.
